org.apache.river.mercury

Class MailboxImpl.NotifyTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.river.thread.RetryTask
      • org.apache.river.mercury.MailboxImpl.NotifyTask
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable, java.util.concurrent.Future, java.util.concurrent.RunnableFuture, TimeConstants, FutureObserver.ObservableFuture
    Enclosing class:
    MailboxImpl

    class MailboxImpl.NotifyTask
extends RetryTask
    A task that represents an event notification task for a particular registration. A NotifyTask will be returned to the task pool after one of the following has occured (which ever comes first):
    • The event was successfully delivered
    • The task expires after MAX_TIME has elapsed
    • The task quits after MAX_ATTEMPTS unsuccessful delivery attempts
    • The event could not be successfully retrieved from the registration's event loG iterator.
